This paper is primarily focused on the design and implementation of a traffic engineering application for Software Defined Networks (SDN), which falls under the category of Networked and Internet-based Systems (cs.NI). However, the application also incorporates cognitive capabilities to optimize the routing paths, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). Additionally, the application involves the use of control systems and optimization algorithms to improve network performance (cs.SY, cs.CR). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of information theory to reduce the monitoring overhead required for optimal path selection (cs.IT).
